HEADWORD: Carbolic
<hw>Car*bol"ic</hw> <pr>(k⟦aum⟧r*b⟦ocr⟧l"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>carbo</ets> coal + <ets>oleum</ets> oil.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid derived
from coal tar and other sources; <as>as, <ex>carbolic</ex> acid (called
also <xex>phenic acid</xex>, and <xex>phenol{1}</xex>)</as>. See
<er>Phenol</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carbolic acid</ent>⟦br⟧
